  <main class="content">
    <h2 id="authentication">Authentication</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">DarkLion APIs support two authentication methods: JWT tokens (for the web app) and API keys (for Viktor and external integrations). For Viktor, always use an API key.</p>

    <div class="auth-box">
      <strong style="color:#c9a84c;">API Key Authentication</strong><br>
      Include your API key in the <code>Authorization</code> header as a Bearer token.<br><br>
      <code>Authorization: Bearer dlk_your_api_key_here</code>
    </div>

    <p>API keys are generated in <strong>Settings → API Keys</strong>. Each key has full admin access to the firm's data. Keys start with <code>dlk_</code> and are shown only once at creation — store them securely.</p>

    <h2 id="base-url">Base URL</h2>
    <p>All API endpoints are relative to:</p>
    <pre>https://darklion.ai</pre>
    <p>Or your firm's custom subdomain if configured (e.g., <code>https://my.sentineltax.co</code>).</p>

    <h2 id="errors">Errors</h2>
    <p>The API uses standard HTTP status codes. Error responses return JSON:</p>
    <pre>{ "error": "Human-readable error message" }</pre>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>400</td><td>Bad request — missing or invalid parameters</td></tr>
        <tr><td>401</td><td>Unauthorized — invalid or missing API key</td></tr>
        <tr><td>403</td><td>Forbidden — you don't have access to this resource</td></tr>
        <tr><td>404</td><td>Not found — resource doesn't exist</td></tr>
        <tr><td>500</td><td>Server error — something went wrong on our end</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="viktor-context">Viktor Context</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The Viktor context endpoint is the primary tool for Viktor's morning briefings. It returns a complete snapshot of the firm's current state in a single request — pipeline status, urgent items, and everything that needs attention.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/viktor/context</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Returns a comprehensive snapshot of the firm for Viktor's daily briefing. No parameters required.</p>
    <p><strong>Response fields:</strong></p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>firm_summary</td><td>object</td><td>Total counts: relationships, people, companies, open threads, MRR</td></tr>
        <tr><td>pipeline.by_stage</td><td>object</td><td>Pipeline jobs grouped by stage name, each with entity/relationship info</td></tr>
        <tr><td>pipeline.total_active</td><td>number</td><td>Total active pipeline jobs</td></tr>
        <tr><td>urgent.unsigned_tax_returns</td><td>array</td><td>Tax returns sent but not yet signed, with days waiting</td></tr>
        <tr><td>urgent.stalled_messages</td><td>array</td><td>Message threads with no staff reply for 48+ hours</td></tr>
        <tr><td>urgent.open_proposals</td><td>array</td><td>Proposals in sent/viewed status</td></tr>
        <tr><td>needs_attention.new_clients_no_pipeline</td><td>array</td><td>New relationships (last 30 days) with no pipeline job</td></tr>
        <tr><td>needs_attention.expiring_engagements</td><td>array</td><td>Engagement letters expiring within 60 days</td></tr>
        <tr><td>needs_attention.birthdays_this_month</td><td>array</td><td>Clients with birthdays this month</td></tr>
        <tr><td>recent_activity</td><td>array</td><td>Tax delivery activity in the last 7 days</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="relationships-list">Relationships</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Relationships are the top-level client groupings. Each relationship can have multiple people and companies attached to it.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/relationships</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all relationships for the firm. Supports search and filtering.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>search</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Filter by relationship name</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="relationships-get"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/relationships/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get a single relationship with all associated people and companies.</p>

    <h3 id="relationships-snapshot"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/relationships/:id/snapshot</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get a rich snapshot of a relationship including recent tax deliveries, message threads, activity feed, and active engagement letters.</p>

    <h2 id="people-list">People</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Individual people attached to relationships. People can be portal users, signers on tax returns, and message recipients.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/people</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all people for the firm.</p>

    <h3 id="people-get"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/people/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get a single person with full details.</p>

    <h3 id="people-update"><span class="method method-put">PUT</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/people/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Update a person's details. Send only the fields you want to update.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>first_name</td><td>string</td><td>First name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>last_name</td><td>string</td><td>Last name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>email</td><td>string</td><td>Email address</td></tr>
        <tr><td>phone</td><td>string</td><td>Phone number</td></tr>
        <tr><td>notes</td><td>string</td><td>Internal staff notes</td></tr>
        <tr><td>portal_enabled</td><td>boolean</td><td>Enable/disable portal access</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="companies-list">Companies</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Companies are business entities attached to relationships. Tax deliveries and documents are often associated with companies.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/companies</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all companies for the firm.</p>

    <h3 id="companies-get"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/companies/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get a single company with full details including linked people.</p>

    <h2 id="messages-list">Messages</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The messaging system uses threads. Each thread belongs to a person and contains a history of messages between staff and client.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/messages</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List message threads.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>person_id</td><td>number <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Filter by person</td></tr>
        <tr><td>status</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>open | closed</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="messages-reply"><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/messages/:threadId/reply</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Send a reply to an existing message thread.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>body</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>Message body text</td></tr>
        <tr><td>internal</td><td>boolean <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>If true, message is internal note only (not sent to client)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="messages-create"><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/messages</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Create a new message thread.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>person_id</td><td>number <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>Person to message</td></tr>
        <tr><td>subject</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>Thread subject</td></tr>
        <tr><td>body</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>Initial message body</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="docs-list">Documents</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Documents are stored in S3 and organized by owner (person or company), year, category (tax/other), and section (firm_uploaded or client_uploaded).</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/documents</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List documents.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>owner_type</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>person | company</td></tr>
        <tr><td>owner_id</td><td>number <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>ID of the person or company</td></tr>
        <tr><td>year</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Filter by tax year e.g. "2025"</td></tr>
        <tr><td>folder_category</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>tax | other</td></tr>
        <tr><td>folder_section</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>firm_uploaded | client_uploaded</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="docs-move"><span class="method method-put">PUT</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/documents/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Update document metadata including moving between folders.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>display_name</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Rename the document</td></tr>
        <tr><td>year</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Move to a different tax year folder</td></tr>
        <tr><td>folder_section</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>firm_uploaded | client_uploaded</td></tr>
        <tr><td>folder_category</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>tax | other</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="docs-delete"><span class="method method-delete">DELETE</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/documents/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Permanently delete a document from S3 and the database.</p>

    <h2 id="pipeline-jobs">Pipelines</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Pipelines track workflow progress for clients. Each client entity (person or company) can have one or more pipeline jobs moving through stages.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/pipelines/jobs</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List active pipeline jobs. Returns jobs with their current stage, entity, and relationship info.</p>

    <h3 id="pipeline-move"><span class="method method-put">PUT</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/pipelines/jobs/:id</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Update a pipeline job — most commonly used to advance to the next stage.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>current_stage_id</td><td>number <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>ID of the new stage to move the job to</td></tr>
        <tr><td>status</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>active | complete | archived</td></tr>
        <tr><td>title</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-optional">optional</span></td><td>Update job title</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>To advance a job to the next stage, you need the stage ID. Get stages for a pipeline template with <code>GET /api/pipelines/templates/:id/stages</code> (see below).</p>

    <h3 id="pipeline-stages"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/pipelines/templates/:id/stages</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all stages for a pipeline template, ordered by position. Use this to get stage IDs for moving jobs.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>id</td><td>number</td><td>Stage ID — use this in PUT /jobs/:id to move a job</td></tr>
        <tr><td>name</td><td>string</td><td>Stage name (e.g. "CPA Return Review")</td></tr>
        <tr><td>position</td><td>number</td><td>Order in the pipeline (0 = first)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>color</td><td>string</td><td>Stage color for UI display</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="tax-list">Tax Deliveries</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Tax deliveries are the end-to-end workflow for delivering a completed tax return to a client for review and e-signature.</p>

    <p><strong>Delivery statuses:</strong> <code>draft</code> → <code>sent</code> → <code>approved</code> → <code>signed</code> → <code>complete</code>. If changes requested: <code>needs_changes</code>.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/tax-deliveries</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List tax deliveries for a company or person.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>company_id</td><td>number</td><td>Filter by company (use one of these)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>person_id</td><td>number</td><td>Filter by person</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="tax-send"><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/tax-deliveries/:id/send</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Send a draft tax delivery to the client. This notifies signers via email and creates a portal message thread. Delivery must be in <code>draft</code> status.</p>

    <h3 id="tax-summary"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/tax-deliveries/:id/summary</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get the AI-generated tax summary for a delivery (if generated).</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>status</td><td>string</td><td>none | processing | completed | error</td></tr>
        <tr><td>data</td><td>object | null</td><td>Full ReportData object when completed (see Tax Summary Schema below)</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/tax-deliveries/:id/generate-summary</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Trigger AI analysis of the attached PDF. Runs asynchronously — poll <code>/summary</code> for status. Requires a review document to be attached.</p>

    <h2 id="proposals-list">Proposals</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">Proposals are the engagement letter / service agreement workflow. Clients select a tier, provide their info, and e-sign the LOE.</p>

    <p><strong>Proposal statuses:</strong> <code>draft</code> → <code>sent</code> → <code>viewed</code> → <code>accepted</code> → <code>signed</code></p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/proposals</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all proposals for the firm. Supports filtering by status.</p>

    <h3 id="proposals-stats"><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/proposals/stats</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get proposal statistics: total, sent, accepted/signed, and signed MRR.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>total</td><td>number</td><td>Total proposals</td></tr>
        <tr><td>sent</td><td>number</td><td>Proposals in sent status</td></tr>
        <tr><td>accepted_signed</td><td>number</td><td>Proposals accepted or signed</td></tr>
        <tr><td>mrr</td><td>number</td><td>Monthly recurring revenue from signed engagements</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="viktor-session">Viktor Chat</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The Viktor Chat API powers the live AI assistant in the DarkLion dashboard. Viktor has full access to firm context and can hold conversations with staff. Sessions are per-user per-day and auto-purge after 3 days. <strong>Note:</strong> These endpoints require JWT authentication (staff login) because Viktor needs a <code>userId</code> to store per-user sessions. API token auth is not supported here.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/viktor-chat/session</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Get or create today's session for the current user. Returns the session record including any existing messages. Also triggers 3-day cleanup of old sessions.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>id</td><td>number</td><td>Session ID</td></tr>
        <tr><td>session_date</td><td>string</td><td>Today's date (YYYY-MM-DD)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>messages</td><td>array</td><td>Array of message objects with role, content, timestamp</td></tr>
        <tr><td>briefing_generated</td><td>boolean</td><td>Whether morning briefing has been generated today</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3 id="viktor-briefing"><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/viktor-chat/briefing</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Generate Viktor's morning briefing for today. Pulls full firm context (<code>/api/viktor/context</code>), sends to Claude Haiku, and stores the result. Only generates once per day — subsequent calls return the cached briefing.</p>
    <p>No request body required. Response:</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>messages</td><td>array</td><td>Session messages including the new briefing</td></tr>
        <tr><td>already_generated</td><td>boolean</td><td>True if briefing was cached from an earlier call today</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/viktor-chat/briefing-for/:userId</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Viktor uses this to push a personalized morning briefing into a specific staff member's chat session. Accepts API token auth — Viktor can call this with his <code>dlk_</code> token. Get user IDs from <code>GET /api/staff</code>. Only generates once per day per user; subsequent calls return the cached briefing.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>userId (path)</td><td>number <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>firm_users.id of the staff member to brief</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Response: <code>{ ok, user, messages, already_generated }</code></p>

    <h3 id="viktor-message"><span class="method method-post">POST</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/viktor-chat/message</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">Send a message to Viktor. Viktor receives the full current firm context plus the last 20 messages of conversation history on every call, then responds via Claude Haiku. Response is stored in the session.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>message</td><td>string <span class="badge badge-required">required</span></td><td>The user's message text</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Response:</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>reply</td><td>string</td><td>Viktor's response text</td></tr>
        <tr><td>messages</td><td>array</td><td>Full updated conversation history for this session</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2 id="staff-list">Staff</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">The staff endpoint returns all accepted firm users. Viktor uses this to build per-staff task lists and assignments.</p>

    <h3><span class="method method-get">GET</span> <span class="endpoint-path">/api/staff</span></h3>
    <p class="endpoint-desc">List all accepted staff users for the firm.</p>
    <table class="params-table">
      <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>id</td><td>number</td><td>User ID</td></tr>
        <tr><td>name</td><td>string</td><td>Full name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>display_name</td><td>string</td><td>Display/preferred name</td></tr>
        <tr><td>email</td><td>string</td><td>Email address</td></tr>
        <tr><td>role</td><td>string</td><td>owner | admin | staff</td></tr>
        <tr><td>last_login_at</td><td>string</td><td>Last login timestamp</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

